ganizer for the IWW, a turbulent romance, and her struggle to support herself and her child.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aJewish womenzUnited StatesvBiography. 0aLabor unionsxOrganizingzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aWomen immigrantszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aWomen in the labor movementzUnited StatesvBiography. 4aBiography & Autobiography. 4aLabor History. 4aWomens Studies.  aequal rights, equal pay, sexual and personal autonomy, intra-union dynamics, immigration experience, labor activism.1 aDeVault, Ileen A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHenderson, Robbin Légère, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066587140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150170948740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501709487423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501709487/original  a978-3-11-066587-1  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles